    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @felix2feng. When an operation has a a return value, `SafeERC20` interprets it exactly as Solidity would, for backwards compatibility. If a contract returns a non-zero number in place of a bool, Solidity will interpret it as `true`, and so `SafeERC20` considers it a success and does not revert.\r\n\r\nYou're right that the comment is not accurate. We should change it to reflect the actual semantics.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/cf7375d6b873afc9f705e329db39e2ef389af9d2/contracts/token/ERC20/SafeERC20.sol#L48\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what Set are doing but IMO a return value of 4 should not be considered a failure.",
